@startuml
title YPS CSV Import & 7AM Scheduler (Simplified View)

hide footbox
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor ImportService as IMP
participant YPS_FileServer as YFS
participant "SaleService" as SS

database import_record as IR
note right of IR
Import summary:
accestime, importstatus,
activeSessionCount, failedTxCount,
filename, totalTxCount, isEmailSent,
importStartAt, lastEmailSentAt, remark
end note

database import_session as IS
note right of IS
must column for import session table
session_id, store_id
end note

database CDSG_ESERVICEHEADERTABLE as SH
database SaleTransaction as ST

database yps_integration as YPS
note right of YPS
Failure tracking:
status=FAIL
fromOnline=true (API realtime)
fromOnline=false (CSV/manual import)
end note

database workshift as WT

actor "ShiftTxShceduler" as SCH
participant MailService as MAIL
participant MailConfig as MC
note right of MC
Mail configuration source:
Table:mail_config
-provider ,username ,password ,remark
Table: mail_template
- template_id ,subject ,content , mail_for = 'FAIL_MAIL' ,cc_mails ,bcc_mails

Table: mail_participant
- template_id (FK),recipient_email
EmailContent:Only add TransactionNumber as CSV
end note
== IMPORT PROCESS ==

IMP -> YFS: Fetch CSV File
YFS --> IMP: Return CSV Data

note right of IMP
CSV may contain multiple stores and tx.
Example: 3 stores x 3 transactions each
end note

IMP -> IR: Insert import_record\n(status=PROCESS,\nactiveSessionCount=0,filename,totalTxCount=0,\nfailedTxCount=0,\nisEmailSent=false,\nimportStartAt=now)

IMP -> YPS :insert tx record(isOnline=false)(true is only for normal process)
note right of IMP
For each store:
- Create 1 Sale Header
- Create 1 Import Session (ACTIVE)
- activeSessionCount++
end note
IMP -> IR:updateTransactionCount(
IMP -> SH: Create Sale Header (storeId)
SH --> IMP: saleHeaderId

IMP -> IS: Insert Import Session (ACTIVE)
IS --> IMP: OK

IMP -> IR: Update activeSessionCount +1
IR --> IMP: OK



IMP -> SS: processSaleTransaction()

alt Success
    SS -> ST: Store sale info
    SS --> IMP: success
else Failed
    SS -> YPS: Insert/Update failed record\n(status=FAIL, fromOnline=false)
    SS --> IMP: failed
    IMP -> IR: Update failedTxCount +1
end

SS --> IMP: result (success/fail)

IMP -> IR: Update Import status=Success,\ncompletedAt=now
IR --> IMP: OK

== 7AM SHIFT CHECK ==

SCH -> IR: Check import_record where activeSessionCount > 0
note right of IR
may be you found totalActiveSessionCount as 5 (3 is from wed and 2 is today)
- Find in sale table where status is not process and fromOnline=false
- and decrease activesesssioncount base on import_session
end note
IR --> SCH: return result

note right of SCH
For each active session:
Check if any SaleTransaction status=PROCESS and fromOnline=false
If PROCESS exists -> close shift and session,
then activeSessionCount--
end note

SCH -> ST: Check any status=PROCESS (per session/store) in sale and  check workshift which is still open
ST --> SCH: exists? (true/false)

alt PROCESS found
    SCH -> WT: Close Workshift
    WT --> SCH: OK
    IS --> SCH: OK
    SCH -> IR: Decrease activeSessionCount
    IR --> SCH: OK
else No PROCESS
    note right: No action needed
end

== 7AM FAILED EMAIL CHECK ==

SCH -> IR: Find failedTxCount > 0 AND isEmailSent=false
IR --> SCH: candidates


note right of SCH
Date range:
from = lastEmailSentAt (or importStartAt)
to = now
Fetch FAIL records where fromOnline=false
end note

SCH -> YPS: Fetch failed records\n(status=FAIL, fromOnline=false,\nfailAt between from..to)
YPS --> SCH: failed list

alt Fail records exist
    SCH -> MAIL: Send failure report (failed list)
    MAIL -> MC: Load SMTP config
    MC --> MAIL: config
    MAIL --> SCH: Email sent

    SCH -> IR: Update isEmailSent=true,\nlastEmailSentAt=now
    IR --> SCH: OK
else No failed record
    note right: No email sent
end

@enduml


